                    "description": "I am passionate about natural resource governance in a global context. How are today\u2019s international trends impacting upon rural livelihoods of people who depend upon those resources? In relation to this question I obtained most of my experiences through assignments that included \n\u2022\tlocal governance as a multi stakeholder partnership to address the impacts of (international) companies in the forest (2008), mining (2010 and 2017) and water sector (2017-2018) in DRC on rural livelihoods\n\u2022\tevaluations of international lobby and advocacy programs on minerals in DRC (2017), improved land governance and on food and beverage companies to make their supply chains sustainable (2012-2015). \n\u2022\tassessing the role of the state in the governance of the global palm oil sector (2014-2015).\n\u2022\tassessing the impact of the export oriented mango sector of Burkina Faso on land tenure, gender, labour conditions and child labour, household food and nutrition security etc. (2017). \nAs of 2016, due to my experiences in theory based evaluations I have become a member of the external reference group of both Oxfam Novib and ICCO to advice on the monitoring and evaluation of the Dutch Strategic Partnership programme on civil society strengthening for lobby and advocacy. \nIn the 2016 -2018 period I advised the transboundary Water4Virungas project in Rwanda, Uganda and Eastern DRC on water governance and conflict transformation related to natural resources",
                    "title": "Senior Advisor Governance and Rural Livelihoods",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
